
some of this can also be found here:
      http://carma.astro.umd.edu/wiki/index.php/Ca_install:  

step 0
-------

grab this software. Should be in ftp://ftp.astro.umd.edu/progs/carma/ca_install.tar.gz
e.g.this gets the tar file, and also cvs updates it with the latest release. Check
the VERSION file 
	
	wget ftp://ftp.astro.umd.edu/progs/carma/ca_install.tar.gz
	tar zxf ca_install.tar.gz
	cd ca_install
	cvs login
	cvs up


step 1:
-------
confirm you have basic things installed


	./configure



step 2:
-------
test a bunch of hello world programs

	cd Hello_World
	make -i tests
	


step 2a:
--------

you can test predefined binaries, e.g. (ARCH= is optional)

	make test2 ARCH=Linux_i686
